    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-03-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-03-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="79"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_PPS1">PPS</gloss> files, lot 64 D 563, “Atomic
                    Energy–Armaments 1952–1953”</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Executive Secretary of the National Security
                        Council (<persName corresp="#p_LAYJSJ1" type="from">Lay</persName>) to the
                            <gloss type="to">
                            <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Senior Staff</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d79fn1">Copies were transmitted to Dr. <persName
                            corresp="#p_BUSHDV1">Vannevar Bush</persName> of the Panel of
                        Consultants and to the members of the <hi rend="italic">Ad Hoc</hi>
                        Committee designated in this memorandum.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-03-12">March 12,
                            1953</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list type="subject">
                    <item>Subject:</item>
                    <item>Armaments and American Policy</item>
                </list>
                <list type="references">
                    <head>References:</head>
                    <label>A.</label>
                    <item>Memo for Senior <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Staff from Executive
                        Secretary, same subject, dated February 4, 1953<note n="2" xml:id="d79fn2">
                            <persName corresp="#p_LAYJSJ1">Lay</persName>’s memorandum transmitted
                            to the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Senior Staff the Report by
                            the Panel of Consultants, <ref target="#pg_1056">p. 1056</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>B.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Action No. 725<note n="3"
                            xml:id="d79fn3">For <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Action No. 725,
                            see footnote 6, <ref target="#pg_1114">p. 1114</ref>.</note>
                    </item>
                    <label>C.</label>
                    <item>Record of Meeting of Senior <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Staff,
                        March 2, 1953, item 3<note n="4" xml:id="d79fn4">The record of meeting
                            indicates that the Senior Staff “Discussed procedure for preparing the
                            reports called for by <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> Action No.
                            724–b and constituted an ad hoc committee, composed of State, Defense,
                                <gloss target="#t_AEC1">AEC</gloss>, <gloss target="#t_CIA1"
                                >CIA</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_PSB1">PSB</gloss> representatives
                            (with Civil Defense participation as required), to consult Dr. <persName
                                corresp="#p_BUSHDV1">Vannevar Bush</persName> and prepare an initial
                            draft report for consideration by the Senior Staff with the
                            participation of Dr. <persName corresp="#p_BUSHDV1">Bush</persName>.”
                                (<gloss target="#t_SP1">S/P</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                                >NSC</gloss> files, lot 62 D 1, “Planning Board Meetings
                            1953–1954”)</note>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>It will be recalled that the National Security Council at its 134th meeting
                    directed the Senior Staff, with the assistance of Dr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_BUSHDV1">Vannevar Bush</persName>, to report to the Council on
                    possible means of carrying out the recommendations of the Department of State
                    Panel of Consultants on Disarmament, as contained in the report circulated by
                    the reference memorandum of February 4. The Senior Staff constituted an <hi
                        rend="italic">ad hoc</hi> committee to prepare an initial draft report for
                    consideration by the Senior Staff with the advice and assistance of Dr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_BUSHDV1">Bush</persName>.</p>
                <p>The following officials have been designated to serve on the <hi rend="italic">ad
                        hoc</hi> committee: <list>
                        <item>State—<persName corresp="#p_ARNESONRG1">Gordon Arneson</persName>
                            (Chairman), <persName corresp="#p_FERGUSONJH1">John Ferguson</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Defense—<persName corresp="#p_NOYESCP1">Charles P. Noyes</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_AEC1">AEC</gloss>—<persName corresp="#p_SNAPPRB1">Roy
                                B. Snapp</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_CIA1">CIA</gloss>—<persName>William P.
                                Bundy</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_PSB1">PSB</gloss>—<persName corresp="#p_CRAIGHS1"
                                >Horace S. Craig</persName>
                        </item>
                        <item>Executive Secretary—<persName corresp="#p_WATTSPH1">Philip H.
                                Watts</persName>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>To initiate preparation of the report called for by the Council, “Armaments and
                    American Policy, is being scheduled as item 1 on the agenda for the meeting of
                    the Senior Staff on Monday, March 16, 1953 at 2:30 p.m.<note n="5"
                        xml:id="d79fn5">See summary of meeting, <hi rend="italic">infra</hi>.</note>
                    Dr. <persName corresp="#p_BUSHDV1">Bush</persName> and the <hi rend="italic">ad
                        hoc</hi> committee are being invited to participate in the meeting on this
                    item.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LAYJSJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">James S. Lay, Jr.</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
